<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Join conditions are optional.  The following query is legal by the standard and is support by all RDBMS brands:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
SELECT * FROM table1 JOIN table2
</code></pre>

<p>This is particularly common for NATURAL JOIN, because the join condition is implicitly an equi-join between columns with the same name in the two tables.  It is also ordinary for a CROSS JOIN to have no ON clause.</p>

<p>Change Zend_Db_Select to permit an absent ON clause.</p>

